The paper deals with the problem of computing functions of correlated data while keeping a private function concealed from an eavesdropper. This involves information theory, cryptography, and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
